name: Photograph of your choice printed and mounted.
description:
Although I've pre-printed and mounted a selection of the most commercial images from my website there are thousands to choose from and everyone like's something different, so take a browse through my website (www.louiswalpole.com) look through the different portfolios to see different meets/shows/shoots and send me through a link to the image, I can then print it onto premium glossy photo paper with professional quality Epsom inks before getting it professionally mounted and dispatched to you. 

Obviously this whole process take's a little time so please allow a weeks turn around on an un-mounted print and a fortnight on a mounted print. Also bear in mind that some photos are cropped to dimensions that won't fit A4/A3 ratios - but we can sort something if this is the case. I can also do different sizes if you need - again just drop me a message (louiswalpole@gmail.com)

name: Ratty Camper Mounted Print.
description:
This shot was taken at the Wheels Day show in April '12, it's a HDR shot (High Dynamic Range) a technique which involves 9 individual source images and hours of editing, but results in a rich, vibrant image that has that 'extra dimension'. This is the one that everyone seems to love (who doesn't want a Splitty?) With a split screen camper costing £12k up it's a bit indulgent but you can have this photo on your wall from just £10 - it's a start! 

The image is printed on premium glossy photo paper using professional quality Epsom inks - the result is a print that's as rich and vibrant as the on screen version. The print is then mounted (properly, by a professional mounter/framer - not a cheap pre-cut jobbie) and wrapped in a clear plastic film to keep it safe. I'd recommend adding your own frame, but can happily be popped onto the shelf as is. 

The image is available as A4 and A3, but as I print all the images my self there's no reason you can't have a different size - drop me a message (louiswalpole@gmail.com) to discuss.

name: Ratty Camper Greetings Card.
description:
As one of my most popular images, this seemed to be one of the obvious choices for a greetings card - something a bit different for a car enthusiast! I'm actually really impressed with the quality of the cards - they have a lustre finish with a really good print quality. Blank on the inside it's suitable for any occasion and obviously it's supplied with an envelope. This photo is also available as an A4 or A3 mounted print - have a little look at the main shop. 

Also, if you go for the multiple option you're more than welcome to mix and match from any of the other cards available - just drop me an email with which ones you want included (louiswalpole@gmail.com)
